      .box.process_div
        .project_content_div.project_text_div
          .sticky_content
            h3.project_subheader Selecting an Opportunity 
            p
              | Between the three choices, we decided to go with  
              span.highlight integrating a music feature. 
              | This is because Strava lacks a music feature that a lot of their competitors already have. 
            p
              | Not everyone have mp3 files readily downloaded on phones these days, people mainly use streaming services to access music. It doesn't make sense for Strava to make their own music service, so 
              span.highlight collborating with a music streaming service 
              | is probably best for Strava.
            p
              | However, just having music integration doesn't give enough value to stand out from their competitors. A feature that could be paired with the music integration is to get results after a run about how certain songs, playlists, albums affect your run/cycle. Another feature could be to set a certain beat you like to run to, and only have songs play with that beat.
        .project_content_div.sticky_img_div
          img.project_img.no_img(src='img/no-img.png', alt='no image')
          //- p.caption_last (left) Login screen  |  (right) drop down nav bar
      .box.process_div
        .project_content_div.project_text_div
          .sticky_content
            h3.project_subheader Keeping Consistent 
            p
              | We 
              span.highlight analyzed the design elements in the Strava's Android app
              | , like flow of the app, buttons, navigation bars and typography. In order to keep consistent between the two brands, we analyzed Spotify's Android app as well.
            p
              | For consistency's sake, 
              span.highlight Strava's color scheme was kept and Spotify's music interface structure and gestures were kept
              | .This way, Spotify users that decide to use Strava will not have to learn a new interface; and vice versa, when a Strava user decides to use Spotify, they also won't have to learn a new interface.
        .project_content_div.sticky_img_div
          img.project_img(src='img/strava/consistent_1.png', alt='2 screens showing consistency')
          p.caption (left) Screen: Login  |  (right) drop down nav bar
